How can we count number of pods in a namespace ?
#kubectl get pods -n "yournamespacename"
#kubectl get pods -n myspace

How can we create a pod , given base image is nginx ?
#kubectl run "yourpodname" --image="baseimagename" 
#kubectl run myimage --image=nginx 

How do we need know details of a specific pod ?
#kubectl describe pod "yourpodname" -n "yournamespacename"
#kubectl describe pod myimage -n myspace 
-- look for the container row 

How do we know which node that pods are placed on ?
#kubectl get pods -n "yiurnamespacename" -o wide 
#kubectl get pods -n myspace -o wide 

How many containers are part of your pod , Their states & what are the images that they are running on?
#kubectl describe pod "yourpodname" -n "yournamespacename"
#kubectl describe pod myimage -n myspace 
--look at the containers rows 

How can we delete a pod ? 
#kubectl delete pod "mypodname" -n "mynamespacename"
#kubectl delete pod "myimage" -n "myspace" 

Create a new pod with the YAML File ?
#kubectl run "yourpodname" --image="yourbaseimagename" --dry-run=client -o yaml > "yourfilename".yaml 
#kubectl run "myimage2" --image=redis --dry-run=client -o yaml > redis.yaml










